			<h4>
				<a href='http://bugsboysandbooboos.blogspot.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>erica</a> <span>on Tuesday, September 7</span>
			</h4>
			These look super yummy!  I&#039;ll have to make them gluten-free...if possible.  
Also, for those concerned about raw eggs...get your eggs from a local farmer or just someone local who pastures their chickens and sells the eggs.  Salmonella is pretty much found in store-bought eggs...even the cage-free eggs, which simply means they&#039;re not in cages - the conditions can still be gross and a zillion chickens &quot;free-ranging&quot; in a tiny barn.			<div class="clr"></div>
			<p></p>

					</div>
